  "summary": "Learn about .PPAM files and view a list of programs that open them.",
  "developer": "Microsoft",
  "technical_info": {
    "content": [
      "PPAM files were introduced in 2007 with the release of Microsoft Office 2007. The files are similar to PowerPoint PPA add-in files but were int type, but support additional macro capabilities.",
      "Examples of add-ins include icon-insertion tools, interactive audience polls, and QR code generators. PowerPoint add-ins for PowerPoint 2013 to 365 should be located in the following directories, by default:",
      "C:\\​Users\\​[user name]\\​App Data\\​Roaming\\​Microsoft\\​Addins\\​"
    ]
  },
  "how_to_open": {
    "instructions": [
      "You can open PPAM files with Microsoft PowerPoint 2007 or later in Windows and macOS. To open a PPAM file with PowerPoint 365, select File → Open → Browse, then choose \"PowerPoint Add-ins (*.ppam;*.ppa)\" from the format dropdown menu.",
      "To manage your add-ins in PowerPoint 365, select File → Options → Add-ins."
    ]
  },
